article.headline: Morehead St. 71, ETSU 61
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Leon Buchanan scored 23 points and 10 rebounds to lead Morehead State to a 71-61 victory over East Tennessee State on Tuesday night. Maze Stallworth added 22 points as the Eagles (5-8) overcame a 33-29 halftime deficit to snap a five-game winning streak by East Tennessee State (8-4). Down 57-56 with 3:32 to play, Morehead State picked up seven points from Buchannan to close the game on a 15-4 run. The Eagles shot 52.2 percent in the second half (12 of 23). Kenneth Faried tallied 17 rebounds and three blocks. Morehead State outrebounded the Buccaneers 41-28 and had 16 second-chance points. Buchanan was 11-for-11 from the free-throw line. East Tennessee State was led by Courtney Pigram with 23 points and Kevin Tiggs with 21.
